#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:5
msgid "The SAM medication database"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:8
msgid ""
"The Belgian SAM authentic-source database in Resthome: ATC reference, "
"BCFI class, Black Triangle, SmPC/leaflet and the Search SAM wizard for "
"the nursing home (MR/MRS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:12
msgid "What is the SAM database?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:13
msgid ""
"SAM (Source Authentique des Médicaments, the authentic source of "
"medicines) is the official Belgian medication reference database. "
"Resthome ships a copy of it to feed your nursing home (MR/MRS) catalog "
"with reliable data: CNK code, active ingredient, ATC code, BCFI class, "
"leaflets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:15
msgid "Where can I find the SAM database in Resthome?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:16
msgid ""
"Two entry points. Browsing, through the Care app → Configuration → SAM "
"Database. And the \"Search SAM\" import wizard, through the MR/MRS app → "
"Configuration → eHealth Configuration → Search SAM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:18
msgid "How do I add a SAM medication to my catalog?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:19
msgid ""
"Open the Search SAM wizard, search by name or by CNK code, check the rows"
" you want and click Import Selected. The medications are created in your "
"catalog with their SAM data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:21
msgid "What does \"Black Triangle\" mean?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:22
msgid ""
"The black triangle flags a medication under additional monitoring "
"(additional pharmacovigilance). The information is taken from SAM, for "
"guidance, on the reference record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:24
msgid "Does the search work without an eHealth connection?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:25
msgid ""
"Yes. The search relies first on the local copy of SAM, available offline "
"and instantly. The live DICS v5 service is used only as a fallback and "
"requires a certified eHealth connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:27
msgid "How do I update a medication that is already present?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:28
msgid ""
"Run the search again and re-import the row. If the CNK code already "
"exists in the catalog, Resthome updates the existing record instead of "
"creating a second one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:31
msgid ""
"**SAM** (Source Authentique des Médicaments, the authentic source of "
"medicines) is the official Belgian medication reference database. "
"Resthome uses it as the foundation of its **medication catalog**: rather "
"than entering a medication by hand, you search for it in SAM and import "
"it, with its reliable data (CNK code, active ingredient, classification, "
"leaflets)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:37
msgid "Two entry points:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:39
msgid ""
"**Browse** the reference database — **Care** app → **Configuration** → "
"**SAM Database** (read-only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:41
msgid ""
"**Search and import** — the **Search SAM** wizard, in the **MR/MRS** app "
"→ **Configuration** → **eHealth Configuration** → **Search SAM**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "A feature of the eHealth integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:47
msgid ""
"The **Search SAM** wizard is part of Resthome's Belgian eHealth layer. It"
" installs automatically as soon as the medical module and the eHealth "
"module are present, and access is reserved for the **eHealth manager**. "
"Browsing the database (Care → Configuration) remains accessible without "
"that role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:53
msgid "What the SAM database provides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:55
msgid ""
"Every medication in the reference database carries authentic data, useful"
" both for care and for traceability:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "Data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "What it is used for"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**CNK code**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "Belgian pharmacy code (7 digits) that identifies the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**Active ingredient (INN)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "The active substance, in French and Dutch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**ATC code**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid ""
"Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical classification (WHO), with its "
"description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**BCFI class**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid ""
"Pharmacotherapeutic classification from the Belgian Centre for "
"Pharmacotherapeutic Information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**Black Triangle**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid ""
"Flags a medication under additional monitoring (additional "
"pharmacovigilance)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**Form and route**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "Pharmaceutical form and route of administration, in French and Dutch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**SmPC and leaflet**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid ""
"Links to the Summary of Product Characteristics and the patient leaflet "
"(FR and NL)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**BCFI link**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "Direct link to the medication's page on the BCFI website."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid "**Prescription and manufacturer**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:44
msgid ""
"Dispensing status (prescription required) and marketing authorization "
"holder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:70
msgid "A reference copy, not an order"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:73
msgid ""
"Resthome's SAM database is a **local copy** loaded at installation. It "
"helps you identify and document a medication; it manages neither stock "
"nor prices. Those live on the catalog record, once the medication is "
"imported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:78
msgid "Browsing the SAM database"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:80
msgid ""
"From **Care → Configuration → SAM Database**, you browse the reference "
"database in read-only mode. The list shows the CNK code, the name, the "
"active ingredient, the ATC code, the form and the manufacturer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:84
msgid "Use the search bar and filters to narrow down:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:86
msgid ""
"**search** by name (FR/NL), CNK code, ATC code, active ingredient or "
"manufacturer;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:87
msgid ""
"**filters** — **Prescription Required**, **Black Triangle** and **With "
"CNK**;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:88
msgid "**groupings** by ATC code, by form or by manufacturer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:90
msgid ""
"A medication's record details its identification, its classification, its"
" pharmaceutical form, its active ingredient and the links to its official"
" documents (SmPC and leaflet, FR and NL)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:96
msgid "The Search SAM wizard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:98
msgid ""
"The **Search SAM** wizard finds a medication in SAM and adds it to your "
"catalog in one step. Open it through **MR/MRS → Configuration → eHealth "
"Configuration → Search SAM**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:102
msgid "1. Run a search"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:104
msgid "Choose the **search type**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:106
msgid ""
"**By Name** — by brand name or active ingredient (e.g. *Dafalgan*, "
"*Rilatine*);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:107
msgid "**By CNK Code** — by CNK code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:109
msgid ""
"Enter your term in the search field then click **Search**. The search is "
"**accent-insensitive** and handles multiple words (e.g. *Amlodipine "
"5mg*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:112
msgid "Local search first"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:115
msgid ""
"The wizard first queries the local copy of SAM: the response is "
"immediate, even without a connection. If that copy is empty, Resthome can"
" switch to the live **DICS v5** service — but that path requires a "
"certified eHealth connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:120
msgid "2. Choose from the results"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:122
msgid ""
"Results are shown in a table. Each row shows the **CNK** code, the "
"**name**, the **active ingredient (INN)**, the **strength**, the **form**"
" and — in optional columns — the manufacturer, the ATC code, the BCFI "
"class and the SmPC / leaflet links."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:127
msgid ""
"The **In Catalog** column indicates whether the medication is already in "
"your catalog. Those rows appear **in blue**: no need to recreate them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:130
msgid ""
"Check the **Select** box at the start of the row for each medication to "
"import."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:134
msgid "3. Import to the catalog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/soins/sam-base-medicaments.md:136
msgid ""
"Click **Import Selected**. Resthome creates one record in your catalog "
"per checked medication, carrying over the SAM data:"
msgstr ""

